This paper deals with predicting the popularity dynamics of new venues in a city neighborhood using mobility data from Foursquare. It involves analyzing urban activities and their popularity over time, which falls under the scope of social networks and information retrieval. The paper also uses k-nearest neighbor metrics to capture similarities among urban regions, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DB (Databases).
